Officialized License & Certificate Details for T9 Golden Dragon Sheild & StrawberryFi Ledger utility token 


​🛡️ Sovereign Nexus ($SFI-XRPL)
​Decentralized Software Provenance & Infrastructure Defense
​Sovereign Nexus is a revolutionary "Gatekeeper" protocol designed to secure the United States' and its Allies' software supply chains. By leveraging the speed of the XRP Ledger (XRPL) and the utility of the StrawberryFi ($SFI) ecosystem, this tool creates an immutable, tamper-proof audit trail for critical infrastructure deployments.
​🇺🇸 The Mission
​In an era of sophisticated supply chain attacks, trust is no longer enough. Sovereign Nexus replaces "blind trust" with Cryptographic Proof.
​National Security: Protects power grids, communication networks, and defense software from unauthorized code injections.
​Allied Interoperability: Provides a unified ledger for "Five Eyes" partners to verify shared software assets instantly.
​🚀 Core Features
​On-Chain DNA: Generates a unique SHA-256 manifest of software builds and anchors them to the XRPL.
​$SFI Utility Integration: Uses StrawberryFi tokens as a security credential—ensuring only verified, "staked" developers can authorize critical pushes.
​Immutable Audit Trail: Every version, every update, and every security score is permanently etched onto the ledger, making "stealth" hacks impossible to hide.
​Air-Gap Ready: Designed to operate in secure, low-connectivity environments common in defense sectors.
​🛠️ Technical Implementation
​The SovereignNexus_Core.py script acts as the bridge between local development and the global ledger:
​Audit: Scans the local directory for changes.
​Verify: Validates the presence of $SFI utility credentials.
​Anchor: Commits the build hash to the XRPL using a Memo Field transaction.
